This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their improvements. It also involves the use of neural networks for robotic manipulation tasks. Additionally, it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as it focuses on robotic manipulation tasks and improving the efficiency of reinforcement learning algorithms for such tasks. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning algorithms for decision making in an agent. Furthermore, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves the use of visual input for robotic manipulation tasks. Finally, it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the control of a robotic agent to achieve a certain goal.
